public class Graph_Edges<V,E> extends AbstractGraph<V,Edge<V,E>> implements EdgeGraph<V,E>
Represents a graph structure where vertices are connected by edges, with support for edge-specific attributes. This class extends the AbstractGraph class for generic graph behavior and implements the EdgeGraph interface for edge-based operations.

      public void addEdge(Edge<V,E> edge, Predicate<Edge<V,E>> predicate)
      Adds an edge to the graph if it satisfies the given predicate condition. The edge is added to the adjacency bag of its "from" vertex, and an adjacency bag is ensured for the "to" vertex.
      Specified by:

      Parameters:

      predicate - a condition that determines whether the edge should be added to the graph.
